		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_BUILDING_MERCHANTS_GUILD">
			<Text>Merchants Guild</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_BUILDING_MERCHANTS_GUILD_HELP">
			<Text>Each source of [ICON_RES_FUR] Fur, [ICON_RES_SALT] Salt, [ICON_RES_TRUFFLES] Truffles, [ICON_RES_DYE] Dyes and [ICON_RES_WINE] Wine worked by this City produces +1 [ICON_GOLD] Gold.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_BUILDING_MERCHANTS_GUILD_STRATEGY">
			<Text>The Merchants Guild is a Medieval era building which increases a City's [ICON_GOLD] Gold output from several luxuries as well as providing a mild economic boost and an extra potential Merchant slot. It requires a Market and an improved source of [ICON_RES_SALT] Salt, [ICON_RES_FUR] Fur, [ICON_RES_TRUFFLES] Truffles, [ICON_RES_DYE] Dyes or [ICON_RES_WINE] Wine near by to be built.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_BUILDING_MERCHANTS_GUILD_PEDIA">
			<Text>A guild is an association of artisans or merchants who control the practice of their craft in a particular town. The earliest types of guilds were formed as confraternities of workers. They were organized in a manner something between a professional association, trade union, a cartel, and a secret society. They often depended on grants of letters patent by a monarch or other authority to enforce the flow of trade and to retain ownership of tools and the supply of materials.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]--Wikipedia</Text>
		</Row>
	</Language_en_US>
